-- 
Ivory Coast Police Killed by Gunmen, L’Intelligent Reports

-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 
2011-02-23T10:04:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/ivory-coast-police-killed-by-gunmen-l-intelligent-reports.html
Unidentified gunmen in  Ivory Coast ’s
commercial capital, Abidjan, killed at least 10 policemen
yesterday and seized one military vehicle, according to
l’Intelligent d’Abidjan.  Gunfire was heard in the neighborhood of Abobo throughout
the night, the Abidjan-based newspaper reported today.  The suburb is a stronghold of President-elect Alassane Ouattara, the internationally recognized winner of disputed Nov.
28 elections. Incumbent President  Laurent Gbagbo  has refused to
resign, alleging voter fraud.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Abidjan via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 